last_episode_to_air.name: Debut Singles
last_episode_to_air.overview: The queens write, record and perform their debut singles in hopes of being crowned Canada’s next drag superstar. Guest judge is Nelly Furtado.

name: Canada's Drag Race
overview: Drag queens showcase their Canadian charisma, uniqueness, nerve, and talent to become Canada's Next Drag Superstar and to win the $100,000 grand prize.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview:
The first season of Canada's Drag Race was officially announced via World of Wonder's Instagram on June 27, 2019. The show aired on CraveCanada, OutTV, and select territories on WOW Presents Plus.

This season features contestants competing for the title of "Canada’s First Drag Superstar", a cash prize of $100,000 CAD, a crown and sceptre from Amped Accessories and a year's worth of holiday stays with Hilton.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview:
The second season of Canada's Drag Race was unofficially announced on January 6, 2021 via Crave's French Facebook. The post was soon deleted. On January 7, 2021 it was announced that casting for Season 2 was officially open, with deadline of February 8, 2021. On September 14, 2021, the cast was officially announced via social media.

This season features contestants competing for the title of "Canada’s Next Drag Superstar", a cash prize of $100,000 CAD, a crown and sceptre from Amped Accessories and a supply of beauty products from Shoppers Drug Mart.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview:
The third season of Canada's Drag Race was officially announced on November 10, 2021 via Canada's Drag Race's social media. Casting opened the same day, with deadline of December 5, 2021. The cast of Canada's Drag Race Season 3 was officially announced on June 15, 2022.

This season features contestants competing for the title of "Canada’s Next Drag Superstar", a cash prize of $100,000 CAD powered by Trojan,  a crown and sceptre from Amped Accessories and a supply of beauty products from Shoppers Drug Mart.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview:
The fourth season of Canada's Drag Race was unofficially announced on October 19, 2022, when its casting website opened for auditions. However, the website was deactivated shortly after. On November 1, 2022, it was announced by Canada's Drag Race via social media that casting was officially open, with a deadline of November 21, 2022. The cast of Season 4 was officially announced on October 18, 2023, along with a premiere date of November 16, 2023 for the nine episode season.

This season features contestants competing for the title of "Canada’s Next Drag Superstar", a cash prize of $100,000 CAD, a crown and sceptre from Amped Accessories and a supply of beauty products from Shoppers Drug Mart.

episodes.name: Under the Big Top - The Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens perform in the Canada Drag Race original Rusical: Under the Big Top. Special Guest Judge: Hollywood Jade.

episodes.overview: The queens overact in the Spooktacular slasher flick: Screech. Special Guest Judge: Fefe Dobson.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens show off their best celebrity impressions in the iconic Snatch Game. Special Guest Judge: Connor Jessup.

episodes.overview: The Queens write, record, and perform an original pop-country break up bop. Special Guest Judge: Bif Naked.

episodes.overview: The Queens are challenged to showcase three runway looks at the Sinner’s Ball. Special Guest Judge: Gigi Gorgeous.

episodes.name: The Roast of Brooke Lynn Hytes
episodes.overview: The Queens don’t hold back as they roast the one and only Brooke Lynn Hytes. Special Guest Judge: Emma Hunter.

episodes.name: Prom
episodes.overview: The queens pair up with teenagers for a makeover of a lifetime. Special Guest Judge: Mitsou.

episodes.name: The Reunion
episodes.overview: The eliminated queens return to spill the tea of the season with the remaining queens, and all are gagged by a shocking twist.

episodes.name: Queen of the North
episodes.overview: The final queens write, record, and perform a brand-new remix of Brooke Lynn Hytes’ hit song ‘Queen of the North’. The winner of Canada's Drag Race is crowned.

episodes.name: Sidewalk to Catwalk
episodes.overview: To kick off the season, the queens must turn a streetwear look into catwalk couture in this design challenge. Guest Judge is Monika Schnarre.

episodes.name: The Who-Knows
episodes.overview: The queens' comedy skills are tested as they act as presenters at the inaugural ‘Who-Knows’ award show. Guest Judge is Carole Pope.

episodes.name: Ruets
episodes.overview: The queens pair up and lip sync for their lives together in this drag team challenge spectacular. Guest Judges are Hollywood Jade and Vanessa Vanjie Mateo.

episodes.overview: The queens battle it out in this week's design challenge with a twist. Guest Judges are Sarain Fox and Jimbo.

episodes.overview: The queens impersonate their favourite celebrities for the legendary Snatch Game. Guest Judge is Sarain Fox.

episodes.name: Cosmetic Queens
episodes.overview: The queens write and star in a commercial and photo shoot to promote their new makeup line. Guest Judge is Mei Pang.

episodes.name: Squirrels Trip: The Rusical
episodes.overview: The queens star in Squirrels Trip: The Rusical choreographed by Hollywood Jade. Guest Judge is Jeremy Dutcher.

episodes.name: Masquerade Ball
episodes.overview: The queens get crafty and put their design skills to the test to present three marvellous makeovers in this mega Masquerade Ball challenge. Who will be the belle of the ball and who will be left running from the hall? Guest Judge is Lesley Hampton.

episodes.name: True North Strong (and Fierce)
episodes.overview: In this show-stopping finale, the queens must write and record a verse to the iconic track True North Strong (and Fierce) and give the performance of their life. Will there be tears or tiaras as they compete for the crown and the title of Canada’s Next Drag Superstar? Guest judge is Sarah Nurse.
